      "content": "That's a really strong point about the chilling effect. I want to make sure I'm covering the counter-perspective too, just so people don't think I'm ignoring it, but I'm struggling to see how their arguments hold up against the free speech principle. Most people say regulation is needed for \"safety\" or to stop \"misinformation\"—in the context of this philosophical debate, is there any way those arguments are actually legitimate, or are they just excuses to control speech?",
